</strong>Piers Gelly</h3>
<p>It feels like the discourse around AI and ChatGPT has already changed a lot since this essay was published, only five months ago, but I still find it a cogent, humane, and most importantly, curious approach to the thing that&#8217;s about to destroy us. I admire Gelly&#8217;s bravery here, and moreso the thoughtful way in which he presents his questions, both to his students and to us. It even makes me oddly hopeful. <em>â€“Emily Temple, Managing Editor</em></p>
