<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://lithub.com/why-ai-narrators-will-never-be-able-to-tell-a-real-human-story/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Why AI Narrators Will Never Be Able to Tell a Real Human Story</strong></a><br />
Adam Verner</h3>
<p>Naturally, as a writer, a being that relies on clean water, and a person on the internet trying to figure out if Google is telling me the truth about whether my kid has pinkeye or just a pink eye, I think about AI a lot, but I hadn&#8217;t considers its effect on audiobook narration until I read Adam Verner&#8217;s lovely meditation on his own career as a narrator, and what we&#8217;ll lose if we cede the field to AI. It&#8217;s beautiful, thought-provoking, and, given the speed with which we&#8217;re handing over our humanity already, pretty damn melancholy. <em>â€“JG</em></p>
