<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://lithub.com/58-books-you-need-to-read-recommended-by-people-who-know/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>58 Books You Need to Read (Recommended by People Who Know)</strong></a><br />
Literary Hub</h3>
<p>To celebrate Lit Hub&#8217;s 10th birthday (!), we asked a bunch of our friends, contributors, and other literary smarties to tell us about the best book they&#8217;d read in the last 25 years. This is the resultant list, which has a gem or two for anyone looking for a new (old) book. But more importantly, it is a reflection of the community that has sprung up around our little website in the last decade. This year, as the literary ecosystem, both online and off, continues to shrink, I am grateful for all our readers and contributors, as well as the valiant writers, agents, and editors still out there making books for us to read and write about.Â  <em>â€“ET</em></p>
