<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="261100" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/how-black-labor-unions-impacted-the-creation-of-the-stanzaic-blues-poem/longform-banner-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2.png" data-orig-size="1200,600" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="longform banner (2)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2-300x150.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2.png" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-261100" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2.png" alt="" width="1200" height="600" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2.png 1200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2-300x150.png 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2-768x384.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2-60x30.png 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/longform-banner-2-50x25.png 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://lithub.com/how-black-labor-unions-impacted-the-creation-of-the-stanzaic-blues-poem/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>How Black Labor Unions Impacted the Creation of the Stanzaic Blues Poem</strong></a><br />
Kristin Grogan</h3>
<p>I was introduced to the poetry of Langston Hughes through high school English class surveys, but it was a history class that unlocked a deeper reading of his work for me. During the Spanish Civil War, Hughes worked as a war correspondent for the Black press, writing about volunteers who took up the call of solidarity to fight fascists. Reading about Hughes&#8217;s antifascism gave his poems a different tenor for me.</p>
<p>Groganâ€™s essay similarly expanded my reading, interweaving a close analysis of Hughesâ€™s and Sterling Brownâ€™s poems with an attention to class and labor. She situates the poems in their particular moment of Black unionization, alongside famous labor actions like the formation of the Brotherhood of Sleeping Car Porters. As someone who sometimes struggles with poetry, this historical labor angle made for a great way back into Hughes. <em>â€“JF</em></p>
