<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://lithub.com/what-was-literary-twitter-the-bracketwhat-was-literary-twitter-the-bracket/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>What Was Literary Twitter? The Bracket</strong></a><br />
Literary Hub</h3>
<p>This year, at Literary Hub, we finally dipped our toe into something that I have wanted to try for years: brackets. No, I do not watch sports. We started in March with the <a href="https://lithub.com/the-best-villains-in-literature-bracket/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Best Villains in Literature</a> bracket, but I think our fall tournament (?) was even better.Â <em>Be dumber</em>, we told ourselves as we sifted through the internet graveyard of forgotten discourse, broken links, deleted tweets, our own broken brains. <em>It&#8217;s Twitter</em>. Also, <a href="https://lithub.com/what-was-literary-twitter-the-champion/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">the correct Twitter phenomenon won</a>! What I&#8217;m saying is, we had fun. Hope you all did too. <em>â€“ET</em></p>
