<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="254773" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/michelle-de-kretser-i-ask-you-i-beg-you-to-join-us-in-speaking-out-for-palestine/2025-stella-prize-michelle-de-kretser/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser.jpg" data-orig-size="800,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="2025 Stella Prize Michelle de Kretser" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser-300x150.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser.jpg" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-254773" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser.jpg" alt="2025 Stella Prize Michelle de Kretser" width="800" height="400" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser-300x150.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser-768x384.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser-60x30.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-Stella-Prize-Michelle-de-Kretser-50x25.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://lithub.com/michelle-de-kretser-i-ask-you-i-beg-you-to-join-us-in-speaking-out-for-palestine/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Michelle de Kretser: &#8220;I ask youâ€”I beg youâ€”to join us in speaking out for Palestine.&#8221;</strong></a><br />
Michelle de Kretser</h3>
<p>Michelle de Kretserâ€™s acceptance speech for the Stella Prize was the epitome of how an author should approach speaking about the assault on Gaza. She recognizes her fears, she gives them space as well: she says, <em>many of you will be familiar with that voice</em>. She doesnâ€™t say it is something to be ashamed of, it is only something to recognize, and supersede. She acknowledges there is a world in which she could take another route, and give words of empty encouragement to â€œwomen.â€ But to do this without recognizing the suffering of so many women out there would be to ring false: it is not a time to revel, but a time to work hard for others, and give light and space to those whose voices are being erased. <em>â€“JH</em></p>
